Bring a #medium pot{} of water to a boil with a large pinch of @salt{pinch}. Peel the @sweet potato{1%unit}, then dice into ½-inch pieces. Once boiling, add the sweet potato to the pot and cook for about ~{12%minutes}, until fork-tender.

Meanwhile, halve, peel, and finely dice the @red onion{1%unit}. Finely dice the @celery{1%stalk}. Halve the @lemon{1%unit}. Heat @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add the onion and celery and cook, tossing, for ~{5%minutes}, until softened. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then transfer to a #medium bowl{} to cool.

When the sweet potatoes are tender, remove from the #pot{} with a #slotted spoon{} and set aside with the onions and celery. Reduce heat to a low simmer, then add the @skin-on salmon{2%unit} to the water and cook until flakey and opaque, ~{7-8%minutes}. Remove from water and set aside to cool.

With a #potato masher{} or #fork{}, thoroughly mash the sweet potato. Then, mix in the onion, celery, @dried thyme{1%teaspoon}, @panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup}, and @Old Bay seasoning{1%teaspoon} (to taste). Using a fork, flake the salmon into small pieces and mix into the sweet potato mixture. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Form salmon mixture into 8 small patties. Heat @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in the same pan you cooked the onion mixture over medium-high heat. Add the salmon patties and cook ~{2-3%minutes} per side, until golden brown.

Meanwhile, halve the @grape tomatoes{1%bunch} and toss in a medium bowl with the @arugula{2%ounce}, @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, a squeeze of lemon, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Plate a bed of arugula salad and top with the salmon and sweet potato cakes. Finish with a squeeze of lemon and enjoy!